1
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:40,633
<i> Let go of me!</i>

2
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:42,700
<i> Uncle!</i>

3
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:46,233
<i>But what he did to me just
pushed me further away from him.</i>

4
00:00:46,367 --> 00:00:48,700
<i>Mom, weren't you the one
who first pushed him away?</i>

5
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:50,000
<i>- Mom...
- Why can't you understand</i>

6
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,200
<i> my decision?</i>

7
00:00:51,333 --> 00:00:53,433
<i> It's easy to understand</i>

8
00:00:53,567 --> 00:00:56,167
<i>if the man who left you
wasn't involved.</i>

9
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,733
<i> Hello?</i>

10
00:00:57,867 --> 00:00:59,000
<i> Jessica?</i>

11
00:00:59,133 --> 00:01:00,300
<i> Can I talk to Dad?</i>

12
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:02,933
<i>You've got some nerve calling
my child and my husband.</i>

13
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:04,867
<i>- Mom, give it back to me!
- No!</i>

14
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,333
<i> Give that back to her!</i>

15
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:11,667
<i>- You don't listen!
- Please don't hurt my dad!</i>

16
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:14,267
<i> Don't hurt Jessica!</i>

17
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:16,133
<i> I feel sorry for Dad.</i>

18
00:01:16,267 --> 00:01:18,433
<i>Didn't I tell you to stop
calling your father?</i>

19
00:01:18,567 --> 00:01:20,033
<i> His wife is a demon.</i>

20
00:01:20,167 --> 00:01:21,567
<i> I'm leaving for Montreal.</i>

21
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:22,967
<i> Bye.</i>

22
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,000
<i> I have to go.</i>

23
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:26,867
<i>Dad, didn't I make a promise
last time?</i>

24
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,367
<i> We're finally going home.</i>

25
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,333
<i> Let's go.</i>

26
00:01:29,467 --> 00:01:31,400
<i> Jessica?</i>

27
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:32,433
<i> Jessica!</i>

28
00:01:32,567 --> 00:01:34,567
<i> What do we do, Dad?</i>

29
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:38,967
Jessica!

30
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:43,433
What's happening?

31
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:46,567
What's going on?

32
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:48,200
I've been calling you.

33
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:49,567
Don't you hear me?

34
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:51,067
I've been knocking on the door!

35
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:54,400
I've been yelling, and you still
couldn't hear me!

36
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:55,700
What's that?

37
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:57,467
Why are you dressed up?

38
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,433
Are you leaving?

39
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:04,733
Mom, I was fetching Dad
from the bathroom.

40
00:02:04,867 --> 00:02:08,233
That's why I couldn't open
the door immediately.

41
00:02:08,367 --> 00:02:11,533
I'm asking you why
you're dressed up.

42
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:13,267
Are you going somewhere?

43
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:19,667
Yes.

44
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,800
What?

45
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:28,467
I knew it.

46
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:31,167
You're really going to run away
from me? Is that it?

47
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:33,833
So, you took advantage
while I was away? Is that it?

48
00:02:33,967 --> 00:02:36,300
Hazel, stop being
so paranoid.

49
00:02:36,433 --> 00:02:38,267
Why would we even run away
from you?

50
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:41,033
I just wanted to visit...

51
00:02:41,167 --> 00:02:45,333
Mr. and Mrs. Wilson, to thank
them personally.

52
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:49,067
You're still going
to thank them?

53
00:02:49,233 --> 00:02:51,433
They were the reason
why you ended up like that.

54
00:02:51,567 --> 00:02:52,400
After everything they did,

55
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:54,033
you're still going to thank them
in person?

56
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:55,500
What are you even saying?

57
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:58,300
And you didn't mention
anything about this earlier.

58
00:02:58,433 --> 00:03:02,233
Before I left, you didn't even
ask for permission, so...

59
00:03:02,367 --> 00:03:04,367
Why all of a sudden?

60
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:07,600
It's just that we only made
the decision now.

61
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:10,967
And how were we supposed
to tell you?

62
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:13,600
Didn't you take our phones?

63
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:16,200
Right.

64
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:18,733
Speaking of phone...

65
00:03:18,867 --> 00:03:21,100
Here, Jessica.

66
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,400
Jessica, I'm giving you
your phone back

67
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:28,067
because I realized we don't have
any way to communicate.

68
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:31,967
But make sure that when I call,
you answer right away, okay?

69
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:33,267
Do you understand?

70
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:36,233
Because earlier, I kept calling,
knocking for so long,

71
00:03:36,367 --> 00:03:37,567
and none of you opened the door.

72
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,367
You might be the same when it
comes to answering your phone.

73
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:40,567
I'll just take it back
if you do that.

74
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:42,533
Make sure you answer, okay?

75
00:03:42,667 --> 00:03:43,633
Yes, Mommy.

76
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:46,233
And one more thing, just make
sure none of you

77
00:03:46,367 --> 00:03:48,967
contacts anyone, especially in
the Philippines.

78
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,333
I'm telling you. If not...

79
00:03:56,867 --> 00:03:58,200
Hello?

80
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,733
Hello? Yes.

81
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:03,933
I'm sorry.

82
00:04:04,067 --> 00:04:06,667
Yes, I'm on my way.
I just forgot something.

83
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,500
Okay, don't worry.

84
00:04:13,467 --> 00:04:14,933
Okay, bye.

85
00:04:16,067 --> 00:04:17,667
I have to go.
Look, I'm already late.

86
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,933
Follow everything I told you,
Jessica!

87
00:04:42,033 --> 00:04:43,933
I crossed the line, Felma.

88
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,867
What I did was completely wrong.

89
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,533
I wasn't in my element.

90
00:04:50,667 --> 00:04:52,667
I wasn't thinking straight.

91
00:04:54,133 --> 00:04:55,900
Because I was badly hurt.

92
00:04:57,833 --> 00:05:00,867
Noah, I told you, I'm serious.

93
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:03,333
Let's just forget what happened.

94
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:05,833
I know I have my faults too,

95
00:05:05,967 --> 00:05:10,100
so I'm sorry for giving you
false hope.

96
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:15,433
But please, don't try to force
me to change my decision.

97
00:05:15,567 --> 00:05:20,200
I used to say I loved you
for no reason.

98
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,300
But now I know.

99
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:28,733
I love you as a friend.

100
00:05:28,867 --> 00:05:31,000
Just a friend.

101
00:05:32,067 --> 00:05:33,833
And nothing more than that.

102
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,667
I deserve to know the truth.

103
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:40,033
Do you still love Manuel?

104
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:43,400
Is that why you only see me
as a friend?

105
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:52,933
<i>I'm sorry, the subscriber
cannot be reached.</i>

106
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:55,167
Why can't I contact you?

107
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:02,400
Why can't I reach you?

108
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:08,267
I told you to keep me updated!

109
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:19,367
<i>I'm sorry, the subscriber
cannot be reached.</i>

110
00:06:20,767 --> 00:06:22,400
Alice.

111
00:06:26,167 --> 00:06:26,933
Alice.

112
00:06:27,067 --> 00:06:27,933
<i> Yes, friend.</i>

113
00:06:28,067 --> 00:06:29,767
<i>How's the first day
of your seminar?</i>

114
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:31,367
<i> Boring, right?</i>

115
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,100
Well, yes.

116
00:06:33,233 --> 00:06:35,700
But that's not the reason
I called you.

117
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:38,000
It's about Jessica and Manuel.

118
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:39,733
Can you check on them?

119
00:06:39,867 --> 00:06:41,933
I can't reach them.

120
00:06:44,933 --> 00:06:45,933
Okay.

121
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:53,067
I stopped loving Manuel
a long time ago.

122
00:06:53,967 --> 00:06:55,900
Don't you believe me?

123
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,600
I want to believe you, Felma.

124
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:02,367
Trust me, I do.

125
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:05,700
But I don't know.

126
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:08,167
Don't ask me anymore,

127
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:11,567
if you're not going to believe
my answers anyway.

128
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:17,333
Let's just end this, Noah.

129
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:24,267
Just accept what I can
offer you, as a friend.

130
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,333
Like before.

131
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,167
Felma, I can't do that.

132
00:07:29,867 --> 00:07:32,867
You've already shown me
what loving someone means.

133
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,267
That you can still love.

134
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:38,367
For now, I'll give you
the space you need.

135
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,967
To think.

136
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:44,633
But I won't give up, Felma.

137
00:07:49,767 --> 00:07:52,133
We keep going in circles.

138
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,400
I'm sorry.

139
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,033
I'm sorry.

140
00:08:16,067 --> 00:08:17,533
Hello, Jessica?

141
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:19,400
Hello, Miss Felma?

142
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:26,567
Is there a problem?

143
00:08:27,167 --> 00:08:28,567
Is your dad okay?

144
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:29,300
<i> Yes,</i>

145
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:30,700
everything is fine with him.

146
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:33,867
I just wanted to call you
to say that...

147
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,500
Dad and I are here
in the Philippines.

148
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:37,733
<i> We just arrived.</i>

149
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:40,567
You came back?

150
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:41,800
Yes.

151
00:08:41,933 --> 00:08:45,233
But I just wanted to let
you know.

152
00:08:45,367 --> 00:08:47,633
We don't intend to be a bother.

153
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:49,533
As a matter of fact...

154
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:52,267
Dad doesn't know I called you.

155
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,267
<i> I just think you need to know.</i>

156
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,800
Thank you.

157
00:08:57,433 --> 00:09:01,100
Thank you for informing me.

158
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:04,367
I also want to apologize
to Coleen,

159
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,900
for everything my mom said
to her.

160
00:09:07,033 --> 00:09:08,667
It was too much.

161
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:11,867
Even Dad and I can't handle him.

162
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,367
Is the place you're
staying at okay?

163
00:09:15,167 --> 00:09:16,633
Yes, Miss Felma.

164
00:09:16,767 --> 00:09:18,567
<i> Thanks for asking.</i>

165
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,367
Hello?

166
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:22,633
Jessica?

167
00:09:24,433 --> 00:09:26,300
No internet connection?

168
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,600
Jessica?

169
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:34,333
Jessica, dear.

170
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:35,467
I'm done.

171
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,333
Can you please help me?

172
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:39,300
Okay, Dad.

173
00:09:59,867 --> 00:10:01,167
Felma?

174
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:04,167
What's wrong?

175
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:10,633
Are you okay?

176
00:10:10,767 --> 00:10:12,733
Is there a problem?

177
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:32,200
I heard you talking to someone
earlier.

178
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:34,967
Was that Mr. and Mrs. Wilson?

179
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:40,633
Dad, that was Miss Felma.

180
00:10:41,033 --> 00:10:42,000
What?

181
00:10:42,133 --> 00:10:43,533
Why did you call her?

182
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:46,600
I just thought she needed
to know, Dad.

183
00:10:46,733 --> 00:10:48,767
I also want her to feel
our presence

184
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:51,500
because eventually I want
the two of you to meet.

185
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:52,667
Why bother?

186
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:55,033
Dad, I know you really want
to ask

187
00:10:55,167 --> 00:10:58,233
for her forgiveness in person.

188
00:10:58,367 --> 00:11:03,633
And, Dad, honestly, I have
this wishful thinking that

189
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:06,500
maybe I could meet
my older siblings

190
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,600
and build a connection
with them.

191
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:11,833
Dear, come on.
They're mad at me.

192
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:16,600
Can you stop hoping that you'll
have a relationship with them?

193
00:11:17,467 --> 00:11:20,533
Dad, it was just
a wishful thinking.

194
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:23,167
I wasn't really expecting
anything.

195
00:11:23,867 --> 00:11:25,867
What's important to me now

196
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,400
is that we start fresh
with our life here.

197
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:29,900
Isn't that right?

198
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,200
Yes.

199
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:36,200
I hope we made
the right decision.

200
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:40,267
Dad, I know it's scary,
but it's also exciting.

201
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,767
We're free now.
No one can hurt us anymore.

202
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,267
And that's what's important.

203
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:48,733
Dear, you know, you're right.

204
00:11:48,867 --> 00:11:53,100
Instead of being afraid,
we should just be excited.

205
00:11:53,233 --> 00:11:56,733
But you know, there's still
a lot we have to think about.

206
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:58,733
Like your studies.

207
00:11:58,867 --> 00:12:00,833
Dad, don't worry.

208
00:12:00,967 --> 00:12:02,333
I'll look for a cheap school.

209
00:12:02,467 --> 00:12:04,333
- Yeah, and...
- I'll figure it out.

210
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:08,967
We can't stay in this place too
long. We'll run out of money.

211
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:11,600
We need to find
a cheaper apartment.

212
00:12:13,167 --> 00:12:16,767
Also, I'll look for a job.

213
00:12:19,733 --> 00:12:21,633
Dear, the only problem I have
is with my foot.

214
00:12:21,767 --> 00:12:23,733
I can still use my hands.

215
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:26,900
So, I can probably do some
odd jobs here and there.

216
00:12:27,033 --> 00:12:30,467
Right. I'll call Abel and ask
for his help.

217
00:12:36,033 --> 00:12:38,767
Alice, are you in our house now?

218
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:41,033
<i> Friend, no one's answering.</i>

219
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:42,167
The lights are off.

220
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,967
Looks like there's
no one inside.

221
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:45,233
<i> What?</i>

222
00:12:45,367 --> 00:12:46,333
Are you sure?

223
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:48,200
There's really no one.

224
00:12:48,367 --> 00:12:51,267
Hello? Anybody home?

225
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:52,967
- Hello!
- Hey!

226
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:54,533
What are you doing?

227
00:12:54,667 --> 00:12:55,933
<i> Are you a burglar?</i>

228
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:59,133
I'm a friend of a resident here.

229
00:13:01,133 --> 00:13:02,700
Wait.

230
00:13:03,633 --> 00:13:05,100
Are you a Filipina?

231
00:13:05,233 --> 00:13:07,233
<i> Are you an Ilongga?</i>

232
00:13:08,133 --> 00:13:09,400
How did you know that
I'm an Ilongga,

233
00:13:09,533 --> 00:13:11,133
when in fact I speak in English?

234
00:13:11,267 --> 00:13:15,600
Come on. I have many Ilongga
friends. I know that accent.

235
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:18,733
Still sweet even when shouting.

236
00:13:18,867 --> 00:13:20,933
Hello, Alice?
What are you doing?

237
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:22,400
<i>You even have the time to chat.</i>

238
00:13:22,533 --> 00:13:24,467
<i>Go and ask about Jessica
and Manuel.</i>

239
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:29,633
Sis, did you see my friend's
wife and their child?

240
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:32,200
Looks like they're not inside.

241
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:33,900
Yes.

242
00:13:34,033 --> 00:13:36,867
When your friend left,

243
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:40,100
her husband and her child
also left after 10 minutes.

244
00:13:40,233 --> 00:13:44,200
<i> They're carrying luggage.</i>

245
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,833
Oh my!

246
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:48,800
They actually left?

247
00:13:49,367 --> 00:13:51,933
They ran away from me.

248
00:13:52,067 --> 00:13:54,200
Alice, let's meet tomorrow.

249
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:55,400
<i>I'll take the first flight
to Calgary.</i>

250
00:13:55,567 --> 00:13:57,333
Friend, what are you thinking?

251
00:13:57,467 --> 00:13:58,700
What about your conference?

252
00:13:58,833 --> 00:13:59,933
You're just getting
started there.

253
00:14:00,067 --> 00:14:02,667
Will you lose your job
over that?

254
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,700
Well, I don't care.

255
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,100
This isn't acceptable.

256
00:14:06,233 --> 00:14:07,233
I'm going to find Manuel.

257
00:14:07,367 --> 00:14:09,267
They won't be able to run away
from me.

258
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:17,433
Good morning.

259
00:14:17,567 --> 00:14:19,400
Thank you for the coffee.

260
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:25,533
Who's that?

261
00:14:26,933 --> 00:14:30,733
Mr. and Mrs. Wilson,
open the door!

262
00:14:33,067 --> 00:14:35,433
Hazel? What brings you here?

263
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:37,100
Where are Manuel and Jessica?

264
00:14:37,233 --> 00:14:38,400
Manuel!

265
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:40,133
Jessica!

266
00:14:40,267 --> 00:14:42,367
Come out now!
I know you're here!

267
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:44,933
- Manuel! Jessica!
- Friend, calm down.

268
00:14:45,067 --> 00:14:46,867
Where are they? I know you know!

269
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,433
You barged into my home,

270
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:50,667
stomping around like
a crazy woman!

271
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:52,233
And now you're demanding
answers?

272
00:14:52,367 --> 00:14:54,333
No, I don't care!
Where are they?

273
00:14:54,467 --> 00:14:57,767
Even if we knew, we wouldn't
tell you because you're rude.

274
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,000
Really?

275
00:14:59,133 --> 00:15:00,167
Am I?

276
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:01,567
And what about you?

277
00:15:01,733 --> 00:15:04,133
You two are old, wrinkly prunes

278
00:15:04,267 --> 00:15:06,200
sticking your noses into
my family's business!

279
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:08,267
Such a filthy mouth!

280
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:12,267
No wonder Manuel and Jessica
wanted to get away from you.

281
00:15:12,867 --> 00:15:14,867
And we were right
when we helped them

282
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,500
get back to the Philippines.

283
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:18,567
So, Philippines?

284
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:20,367
Where exactly
in the Philippines?

285
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:22,167
We're not telling you
another word!

286
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:23,633
- Get out!
- No!

287
00:15:23,767 --> 00:15:25,400
Not until you tell me
where they are!

288
00:15:25,533 --> 00:15:26,333
Where are they?

289
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:29,033
Leave now, Hazel,
or I will call 911!

290
00:15:29,167 --> 00:15:30,200
I don't care!

291
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:32,300
- I don't care about your 911!
- Friend...

292
00:15:32,433 --> 00:15:33,400
we're not in the Philippines.

293
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:36,833
No! I need to know
where they are!

294
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,133
I'm not yet done!

295
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:53,200
<i>I just wanted to call you
to say that...</i>

296
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:54,833
<i>Dad and I are here
in the Philippines.</i>

297
00:15:54,967 --> 00:15:57,000
<i> We just arrived.</i>

298
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:04,433
Felma.

299
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,133
Felma.

300
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:13,467
Are you okay?
How do you feel?

301
00:16:14,167 --> 00:16:15,333
Let's go. Don't be so lifeless.

302
00:16:15,467 --> 00:16:16,800
Someone is waiting
for you downstairs.

303
00:16:16,933 --> 00:16:18,400
Who?

304
00:16:18,533 --> 00:16:19,833
It's a surprise.

305
00:16:19,967 --> 00:16:22,600
Let's go. You're so beautiful
today. Come on.

306
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:33,200
Yes, Felma, we need to go out

307
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:35,133
because you have
a nice outfit.

308
00:16:35,267 --> 00:16:38,133
We need to flaunt it.

309
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:43,300
Congratulations!

310
00:16:50,933 --> 00:16:53,100
Wait. Wait, wait.
What's the occasion?

311
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:55,933
Why are you
congratulating me?

312
00:16:56,067 --> 00:16:57,367
Is this another ambush?

313
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:59,133
Mom, no.
This is a Thanksgiving dinner

314
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:02,367
because<i> Sisig ni Bunso
</i>was a huge success!

315
00:17:05,867 --> 00:17:07,033
And, Mom, everything we
delivered to the markets

316
00:17:07,167 --> 00:17:11,100
and grocery stores was
completely sold out!

317
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:15,333
Mom, some of them restocked
double, even triple,

318
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:17,833
because people keep looking
for it!

319
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:23,000
Mom's here now.
We can now eat again!

320
00:17:23,133 --> 00:17:25,067
Come on, come on!

321
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:27,767
- Did you all wash your hands?
- Yes, Sir!

322
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:30,333
Okay, let's go! Dig in!

323
00:17:33,667 --> 00:17:35,433
Felma, would you like
some juice?

324
00:17:35,567 --> 00:17:37,033
Would you like some juice?

325
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:44,000
Why aren't Pretty Mommy
and Handsome Daddy

326
00:17:44,133 --> 00:17:45,900
next to each other?

327
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:50,067
Is Dad's gossip true?

328
00:17:50,233 --> 00:17:51,433
Did you two break up?

329
00:17:51,567 --> 00:17:53,033
Aren't you getting
married anymore?

330
00:17:53,167 --> 00:17:54,133
Tetay!

331
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:02,267
Mom, I thought I was going
to be a flower girl.

332
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:04,600
Tetay, you will be
a flower girl,

333
00:18:04,733 --> 00:18:08,067
but at your mom and dad's
wedding.

334
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:26,000
Friend!

335
00:18:26,133 --> 00:18:27,233
Friend, calm down!

336
00:18:27,367 --> 00:18:28,867
- Calm down!
- Calm down?

337
00:18:29,967 --> 00:18:32,500
Manuel and Jessica
ganged up on me.

338
00:18:32,633 --> 00:18:34,500
They are traitors!

339
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:39,100
Move!

340
00:18:39,233 --> 00:18:41,400
What now? You're calling
Jessica again?

341
00:18:41,533 --> 00:18:43,267
She's not even reachable
anymore!

342
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:45,067
Friend.

343
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,700
<i>I'm sorry, the subscriber
cannot be reached.</i>

344
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:49,000
<i> Please try again later.</i>

345
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:53,200
Dear, what are you doing
over there? Come eat.

346
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:56,433
I'm putting
a Philippine SIM card, Dad.

347
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:05,933
Shocks!

348
00:19:06,367 --> 00:19:09,400
My contacts are still
on my Canadian SIM.

349
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:15,933
Dad, I don't have Mr. and Mrs.
Wilson's number memorized.

350
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:24,867
Finally, it's ringing.

351
00:19:27,067 --> 00:19:29,033
Dad, Mom is calling.

352
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,167
Answer it.

353
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:36,967
Answer it, traitors. Answer it.

354
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:39,500
Dad, what do I do?

355
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:43,667
It's up to you if you
want to answer it or not.

356
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:56,233
Answer it.

357
00:19:57,500 --> 00:20:04,200
No! No! No! No!

358
00:20:04,367 --> 00:20:06,633
- Friend...
- No!

359
00:20:06,767 --> 00:20:07,967
Jessica!

360
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:14,833
Pretty Mommy, can you please
take me to the CR?

361
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:17,500
Sure, I'll accompany you.

362
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:18,400
Felma?

363
00:20:18,533 --> 00:20:20,400
- Noah.
- Can we talk?

364
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,700
I can go on my own,
Pretty Mommy.

365
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:26,900
Go ahead and talk.

366
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,167
Is there something
bothering you?

367
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:36,567
Is it about the call
you received at the restaurant?

368
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:40,333
Come on, Felma.

369
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:42,100
I know you.

370
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:46,833
I know when something's
bothering you.

371
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:50,100
Don't worry about me.

372
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:52,633
I'm okay.

373
00:20:52,767 --> 00:20:54,233
Felma, you're not.

374
00:20:55,167 --> 00:20:57,500
Remember when we talked?

375
00:20:58,367 --> 00:20:59,333
You asked me...

376
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:04,200
if we can still be friends.

377
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:05,100
Felma...

378
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,767
I'm here.

379
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:10,400
Your friend.

380
00:21:10,533 --> 00:21:11,900
You can tell me anything.

381
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:14,133
Just like before.

382
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:20,867
I'll listen without judgment,
just like before.

383
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:24,833
So...

384
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:27,633
Is it about Manuel?

385
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:32,300
Because that kind of reaction
from you...

386
00:21:33,367 --> 00:21:36,933
it only happens
when it's about him.

387
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:39,600
Tell me Felma.

388
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:42,333
Did something happen to him?

389
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:47,800
Looks like Pretty Mommy
and Handsome Daddy are now okay!

390
00:21:47,933 --> 00:21:50,033
Mom, I'll take Daisy
and Tetay home.

391
00:21:50,167 --> 00:21:50,900
Uncle.

392
00:21:51,033 --> 00:21:52,933
Jeff, please give me
a ride too.

393
00:21:53,067 --> 00:21:54,767
Looks like your godfather
fell asleep.

394
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,267
He won't be able to pick me up.

395
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,267
Let's go, Godmother.

396
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:58,767
Is that so?

397
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,033
Me also. We'll go together.

398
00:22:00,167 --> 00:22:02,700
- I'll take Tetay home.
- Nice.

399
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:04,067
Come on, let's go, Pretty Mommy.

400
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:04,867
Bye, Handsome Daddy.

401
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,933
- Good night!
- Bye, Uncle.

402
00:22:24,667 --> 00:22:28,267
So, Uncle?
Is Mom still avoiding you?

403
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:31,633
Still no progress?

404
00:22:35,167 --> 00:22:36,800
No, still nothing.

405
00:22:37,633 --> 00:22:39,933
Maybe I should just accept...

406
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,967
that it's really over
between us.

407
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:43,233
No, Uncle!

408
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:45,600
Jeffrey and I have just been
busy with Sisig ni Bunso.

409
00:22:45,733 --> 00:22:48,967
But now that everything's
done, we've got this.

410
00:22:49,133 --> 00:22:51,467
We will talk to Mom.

411
00:23:07,300 --> 00:23:08,967
I won't allow it.

412
00:23:11,667 --> 00:23:14,267
I won't let Manuel
pull one over on me.

413
00:23:15,867 --> 00:23:18,867
He went back to the Philippines
to get back together with Felma.

414
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:21,133
Well, that's not going
to happen.

415
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:25,667
Because I will follow him.
I will also go home.

416
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,733
Wait, what?

417
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,233
What about your work?

418
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:33,967
Well, come to think of it,
you did ditch your conference.

419
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:36,033
You're probably fired.

420
00:23:36,167 --> 00:23:40,533
Friend, why are you still
chasing after Manuel?

421
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,967
Why not?

422
00:23:47,633 --> 00:23:52,100
It's not like you want to keep
the relationship going, right?

423
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:55,367
Manuel is paralyzed.

424
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:57,600
He's useless to you now.

425
00:23:57,733 --> 00:24:00,033
You couldn't even imagine
yourself taking care of him.

426
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:02,967
Why? Because he's just a burden
to you now, right?

427
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:04,367
Remember?

428
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:08,267
You even considered
divorcing him.

429
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,000
Didn't you?

430
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:20,100
Well...

431
00:24:20,233 --> 00:24:22,067
I changed my mind.

432
00:24:26,567 --> 00:24:29,733
He is still my husband,
so he is mine.

433
00:24:30,667 --> 00:24:33,400
And I won't let him get back

434
00:24:33,533 --> 00:24:35,333
with his mistress,
that slutty Felma!

435
00:24:37,367 --> 00:24:39,000
Besides...

436
00:24:40,033 --> 00:24:42,433
I already took out insurance
on him.

437
00:24:42,567 --> 00:24:46,367
So if anyone's going to benefit
from that, it's me!

438
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:48,067
Only me!

439
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,400
Friend, enough of that.

440
00:24:49,533 --> 00:24:50,800
Stop!

441
00:24:50,933 --> 00:24:52,700
- Friend!
- What?

442
00:24:52,833 --> 00:24:53,800
Stop!

443
00:24:55,167 --> 00:24:57,133
And in case you forget...

444
00:24:58,067 --> 00:25:00,000
My child is with him.

445
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:04,033
That's my child, Jessica.

446
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,967
What is he going to do?

447
00:25:07,067 --> 00:25:10,367
Introduce her to Felma?

448
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:12,733
And to his illegitimate kids?

449
00:25:12,867 --> 00:25:13,733
Then what?

450
00:25:13,867 --> 00:25:16,567
They will all be one big
happy family?

451
00:25:16,700 --> 00:25:19,200
No! That's not going to happen!

452
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:22,833
Manuel is such an idiot!

453
00:25:22,967 --> 00:25:25,267
Jessica is not even his kid!

454
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:28,300
I will take them back.

455
00:25:28,433 --> 00:25:31,100
I will take back Manuel
and Jessica.

456
00:25:31,233 --> 00:25:32,533
Remember that, Alice.

457
00:25:32,667 --> 00:25:35,000
I will take them back!

458
00:25:44,433 --> 00:25:48,500
Mom, ever since you and Uncle
Noah talked at the restaurant,

459
00:25:48,633 --> 00:25:50,500
you've always had something
on your mind.

460
00:25:50,633 --> 00:25:52,167
It's about your dad.

461
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:53,933
What happened to Dad?

462
00:25:54,067 --> 00:25:55,133
They are here.

463
00:25:55,267 --> 00:25:56,133
Really, Mom?

464
00:25:56,267 --> 00:25:57,767
We will keep this a secret.

465
00:25:57,900 --> 00:26:00,200
We won't tell Jeffrey
and Andrea.

466
00:26:00,333 --> 00:26:01,433
Andrea, why are you crying?

467
00:26:01,567 --> 00:26:04,567
Coleen's dad is back
in the country again.

468
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:06,500
And Mom and Coleen know.

469
00:26:06,633 --> 00:26:08,267
They are hiding it from us.

470
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,533
One-way ticket to Manila?

471
00:26:09,700 --> 00:26:11,467
I'm going to a war, Alice.

472
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:14,500
And this war is going
to be a long one.

473
00:26:14,633 --> 00:26:16,600
So, are we going to break
the peace in our family,

474
00:26:16,733 --> 00:26:19,033
especially Mom's, just because
you want to see your dad?

475
00:26:19,167 --> 00:26:21,867
If you don't stop,
you have to bear with it.

476
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:24,333
You will lose your sister.
